sourceQuestion:
Which of the following relational calculus expressions is not safe?

A. {t | exists u in R1(t[A] = u[A]) ^ -exists u in R2(t[A] = u[A])}
B. {t | forall u in R1(t[A] = u[A])}
C. {t | -exists u in R1(t[A] != u[A])}
D. {t | exists u in R1(t[A] = u[A]) ^ t[A] = 5}

